  1. AddAndDisplayStrings
  2. DisplayAndRemoveStrings
lastString - The number of the last string to add the queue.

addNumbers

public static void addNumbers()
This test case is for inserting all the numbers (1 <= n <= 100,000 into an empty queue. The numbers are added to the queue using the add(E e) method of the QueueInterface.

removeNumbers

public static void removeNumbers()
This test case is for removing all the numbers (1 <= n <= 100,000 from a fully populated queue. The numbers are removed from the queue using the remove() method of the QueueInterface.

addAndDisplayStrings

public static void addAndDisplayStrings()
This test case is for inserting all the strings starting with "String 1", "String 2" ..... "String 100" to an empty queue. We also display all the queue entries using an Iterator.

DisplayAndRemoveStrings

public static void DisplayAndRemoveStrings()
This test case is for displaying and deleting strings starting with "String 1", "String 2" ..... "String 100" from a fully populated queue. The queue entries are all displayed and deleted using an Iterator.
